---
import PortalLayout from '../../layouts/PortalLayout.astro';
const title = 'Style Guide';
---

<PortalLayout title={title} currentPage="style-guide">
  <div class="page-hero" style="border-left-color: var(--info-gray);">
    <h1>CHAOS PORTAL <strong>Style Guide</strong></h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Design System v3.5</p>
  </div>

  <div class="content">

<!-- INTRODUCTION -->
<div class="section">
<h2>About This Design System</h2>
<p>This design system defines the complete visual language for the Story Coordinate Compass framework. It establishes typography, color, spacing, and component patterns that create consistency across all documentation pages.</p>
<div class="callout callout--editorial">
<div class="icon">!</div>
<div>
<div class="label">CANONICAL SYSTEM</div>
<p>All project pages must conform to these rules. This guide is the single source of truth for visual design decisions.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr/>
<!-- IMPLEMENTATION RULES -->
<div class="section">
<h2>I. IMPLEMENTATION RULES</h2>
<h3>Color Application Rules</h3>
<div class="checklist">
<div><strong>Signal Amber (#F59E0B):</strong> Horizontal Axis ONLY — timeline, position, progression, structure</div>
<div><strong>Clarity Teal (#14B8A6):</strong> Vertical Axis ONLY — depth, dimensions (D0–D5), layers</div>
<div><strong>Info Blue (#3B82F6):</strong> System callouts, general UI elements NOT axis-associated</div>
<div><strong>Warn Red (#EF4444):</strong> Caution states, deprecation notices</div>
<div><strong>Accent Purple (#8B5CF6):</strong> Cross-domain bridges, Creativity Engine elements</div>
<div><strong>UI Colors:</strong> Links, buttons, navigation ONLY — never for semantic content</div>
</div>
<h3>Typography Rules</h3>
<div class="checklist">
<div>H1 uses DM Serif Display at 3.2em — page titles and hero headings only</div>
<div>Body uses system sans stack (Helvetica Neue / system-ui) at 1rem, line-height 1.65</div>
<div>H4 uses Georgia italic for editorial / explanatory subheadings</div>
<div>Monospace (ui-monospace) for coordinates, tokens, and technical notation only</div>
<div>Never use pure black (#000) for text — use var(--text) which adapts to theme</div>
</div>
<h3>Spacing Rules</h3>
<p>All spacing follows an 8px-based scale: xs (8px), sm (16px), md (24px), lg (48px), xl (64px). Maintain consistent rhythm throughout pages.</p>
</div>
<hr/>
<!-- COLOR SYSTEM -->
<div class="section">
<h2>II. COLOR SYSTEM</h2>
<h3>Semantic Colors</h3>
<p>These colors have specific meanings tied to the coordinate system axes:</p>
<div class="color-grid">
<div class="color-card">
<div class="swatch" style="background: #F59E0B; color: white;">SIGNAL AMBER</div>
<div class="color-info">
<div class="color-name">Signal Amber</div>
<div class="color-hex">#F59E0B</div>
<div class="color-usage">Horizontal Axis (story timeline/position)</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="color-card">
<div class="swatch" style="background: #14B8A6; color: white;">CLARITY TEAL</div>
<div class="color-info">
<div class="color-name">Clarity Teal</div>
<div class="color-hex">#14B8A6</div>
<div class="color-usage">Vertical Axis (story depth/dimensions)</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<h3>Information Colors</h3>
<p>These colors indicate system elements unrelated to narrative axes:</p>
<div class="color-grid">
<div class="color-card">
<div class="swatch" style="background: #3B82F6; color: white;">INFORMATION BLUE</div>
<div class="color-info">
<div class="color-name">Information Blue</div>
<div class="color-hex">#3B82F6</div>
<div class="color-usage">System callouts, navigation, general UI</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="color-card">
<div class="swatch" style="background: #6B7280; color: white;">INFORMATION GRAY</div>
<div class="color-info">
<div class="color-name">Information Gray</div>
<div class="color-hex">#6B7280</div>
<div class="color-usage">Editorial notes, meta-information</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<h3>Neutral Palette</h3>
<p>Adaptive neutrals that change with light/dark mode:</p>
<div class="color-grid">
<div class="color-card">
<div class="swatch neutral-primary-bg" style="background: #FAFAFA; color: #000000;">VAPOR</div>
<div class="color-info">
<div class="color-name">Primary Background</div>
<div class="color-hex neutral-primary-bg-hex">#FAFAFA</div>
<div class="color-usage">Page background</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="color-card">
<div class="swatch neutral-surface" style="background: #FFFFFF; color: #000000;">WHITE</div>
<div class="color-info">
<div class="color-name">Canvas Surface</div>
<div class="color-hex neutral-surface-hex">#FFFFFF</div>
<div class="color-usage">Content containers</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="color-card">
<div class="swatch neutral-surface-elevated" style="background: #F1F3F5; color: #000000;">LIGHT GRAY</div>
<div class="color-info">
<div class="color-name">Elevated Surface</div>
<div class="color-hex neutral-surface-elevated-hex">#F1F3F5</div>
<div class="color-usage">Callouts, tables, elevated elements</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="color-card">
<div class="swatch neutral-text" style="background: #222222; color: #FFFFFF;">OBSIDIAN</div>
<div class="color-info">
<div class="color-name">Primary Text</div>
<div class="color-hex neutral-text-hex">#222222</div>
<div class="color-usage">Body text, headings</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<h3>Gradient Usage</h3>
<p>Gradients flow from Horizontal (amber) to Vertical (teal), symbolizing the coordinate system. <strong>Gradients are ONLY used on Compass pages</strong> to reinforce the dual-axis framework.</p>
<div class="gradient-demo gradient-horizontal">
                Horizontal → Vertical Gradient
            </div>
<p><em>Used for: Compass page hero headers, h2 section underlines on Compass pages only. Never use gradients for Library, Home, or Style Guide pages.</em></p>
<div class="callout callout--editorial">
<div class="icon">!</div>
<div>
<div class="label">IMPORTANT</div>
<p>Page headers outside of Compass should use solid gray (var(--info-gray)) for left borders, NOT gradients. Gradients are exclusively for Compass navigation and content.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr/>
<!-- TYPOGRAPHY -->
<div class="section">
<h2>III. TYPOGRAPHY</h2>
<h3>Type Scale</h3>
<p>A clear hierarchical scale ensures readability and visual rhythm:</p>
<div class="type-scale-demo">
<h1>Display Heading (H1)</h1>
</div>
<div class="type-details">
<strong>Font:</strong> Helvetica Neue, 3.2em, 300 weight<br/>
<strong>Usage:</strong> Page titles, main headings<br/>
<strong>Letter-spacing:</strong> -0.03em
            </div>
<div class="type-scale-demo">
<h2>Section Heading (H2)</h2>
</div>
<div class="type-details">
<strong>Font:</strong> Helvetica Neue, 2.2em, 600 weight<br/>
<strong>Usage:</strong> Major section breaks<br/>
<strong>Special:</strong> Gradient underline
            </div>
<div class="type-scale-demo">
<h3>Subsection Heading (H3)</h3>
</div>
<div class="type-details">
<strong>Font:</strong> Helvetica Neue, 1.6em, 550 weight<br/>
<strong>Usage:</strong> Subsections within major sections<br/>
<strong>Letter-spacing:</strong> -0.01em
            </div>
<div class="type-scale-demo">
<h4>Detail Heading (H4)</h4>
</div>
<div class="type-details">
<strong>Font:</strong> Helvetica Neue, 1.125rem, 600 weight<br/>
<strong>Usage:</strong> Detailed subsections, framework names
            </div>
<div class="type-scale-demo">
<h5>Small Heading (H5)</h5>
</div>
<div class="type-details">
<strong>Font:</strong> Helvetica Neue, 1rem, 600 weight<br/>
<strong>Usage:</strong> Minor sections, fine-grained hierarchy
            </div>
<div class="type-scale-demo">
<h5 class="minor-head">Minor Head (H5 Variant)</h5>
</div>
<div class="type-details">
<strong>Font:</strong> Helvetica Neue, 0.9rem, 600 weight, uppercase<br/>
<strong>Usage:</strong> Subsection labels like "Definition", "Examples"<br/>
<strong>Letter-spacing:</strong> 0.04em
            </div>
<h3>Special Typography</h3>
<div class="type-scale-demo">
<div class="subhead">This is a subhead in Georgia Italic</div>
</div>
<div class="type-details">
<strong>Font:</strong> Georgia, 1.1em, 400 weight, italic<br/>
<strong>Usage:</strong> Supplementary explanations below headings
            </div>
<div class="type-scale-demo">
<div class="eyebrow">EYEBROW LABEL</div>
</div>
<div class="type-details">
<strong>Font:</strong> Helvetica Neue, 0.72rem, 600 weight, uppercase<br/>
<strong>Usage:</strong> Category labels, meta-information<br/>
<strong>Letter-spacing:</strong> 0.14em
            </div>
<h3>Body Text</h3>
<p>Body text uses Helvetica Neue at 16px with 1.7 line-height for optimal readability. Paragraphs have 20px bottom margin for breathing room.</p>
<h3>Monospace / Tokens</h3>
<p>Technical notation like coordinates uses monospace: <code>3:00 / D4</code></p>
<div class="type-details">
<strong>Font:</strong> ui-monospace, 0.85em, 700 weight<br/>
<strong>Usage:</strong> Coordinates, technical tokens, code<br/>
<strong>Style:</strong> Token background with border
            </div>
<h3>Source Tags</h3>
<p>Source attribution tags appear inline: <span class="source-tag">COMPASS</span> <span class="source-tag">ORIGINAL</span></p>
<h3>Schema Labels</h3>
<p>Schema labels identify analytical sections and dimension classifiers: <span class="schema-label">Core Dimension 0</span> <span class="schema-label">Archetype Dimension 1</span></p>
</div>
<hr/>
<!-- COORDINATE NOTATION -->
<div class="section">
<h2>IV. COORDINATE NOTATION</h2>
<p>Coordinates are the core technical notation of this system. They always appear as tokens with monospace typography.</p>
<h3>Basic Format</h3>
<p>Standard coordinate: <code>Position / Dimension</code></p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>POSITION</th>
<th>DIMENSION</th>
<th>COORDINATE</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>12:00</td>
<td>Surface Dimension 5</td>
<td><span class="token">12:00 / D5</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>3:00</td>
<td>Psychological Dimension 2</td>
<td><span class="token">3:00 / D2</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>6:00</td>
<td>Cognitive Dimension 3</td>
<td><span class="token">6:00 / D3</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>9:00</td>
<td>Archetype Dimension 1</td>
<td><span class="token">9:00 / D1</span></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h3>Extended Notation</h3>
<p>Multiple coordinates or ranges:</p>
<ul>
<li>Range: <code>3:00-6:00 / D3</code></li>
<li>Multiple: <code>3:00 / D2, D3, D4</code></li>
<li>Vertical stack: <code>6:00 / D0-D5</code></li>
</ul>
</div>
<hr/>
<!-- LAYOUT & SPACING -->
<div class="section">
<h2>V. LAYOUT &amp; SPACING</h2>
<h3>Spacing Scale</h3>
<p>Consistent 8px-based spacing scale:</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>SIZE</th>
<th>VALUE</th>
<th>USAGE</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>xs</td>
<td>8px</td>
<td>Tight spacing, list items, inline elements</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>sm</td>
<td>16px</td>
<td>Paragraph spacing, component padding</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>md</td>
<td>24px</td>
<td>Section spacing, callout margin</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>lg</td>
<td>48px</td>
<td>Major section breaks, header padding</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>xl</td>
<td>64px</td>
<td>Page-level divisions</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h3>Content Width</h3>
<p>Maximum content width: 1100px (centered). Content containers use 50px padding for comfortable reading zones.</p>
<h3>Border Radius</h3>
<ul>
<li>Small (3px): Tokens, inline code</li>
<li>Medium (6px): Callouts, cards, tables</li>
<li>Large (8px): Headers, main containers</li>
</ul>
</div>
<hr/>
<!-- COMPONENTS -->
<div class="section">
<h2>VI. COMPONENTS</h2>
<h3>Sticky Header</h3>
<p>The site header remains visible while scrolling, providing persistent navigation and theme control. It uses a semi-transparent background with blur for depth without obscuring content.</p>
<div class="callout callout--editorial">
<div class="icon">!</div>
<div>
<div class="label">REUSABLE PATTERN</div>
<p>This sticky header pattern is designed to be copied to all pages. Update the <code>aria-current</code> attribute on navigation links to indicate the active page.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h3>Breadcrumb Navigation</h3>
<p>Breadcrumbs show the current page's location within the documentation hierarchy. They appear below the sticky header and use subtle styling to avoid visual competition.</p>
<h3>Callouts</h3>
<p>Callouts highlight important information with contextual color coding and subtle gradient backgrounds for visual depth.</p>
<div class="callout callout--editorial">
<div class="icon">!</div>
<div>
<div class="label">EDITORIAL</div>
<p>Editorial callouts use Information Gray and provide meta-commentary about the framework itself. Note the subtle left-to-right gradient background that creates depth without overwhelming the content.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h3>Axis Callouts (Canonical Pattern)</h3>
<p>Axis Callouts are the <strong>canonical pattern</strong> for all axis-level signaling in v3. They provide clear semantic ownership and visual consistency across all documentation pages.</p>
<div class="callout callout--horizontal">
<div class="icon">→</div>
<div>
<div class="label">HORIZONTAL AXIS</div>
<p>Horizontal Axis Callouts use Signal Amber (#F59E0B) and signal content related to <strong>story timeline, position, progression, and structure</strong>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="callout callout--vertical">
<div class="icon">↓</div>
<div>
<div class="label">VERTICAL AXIS</div>
<p>Vertical Axis Callouts use Clarity Teal (#14B8A6) and signal content related to <strong>story depth, dimensions, and layers</strong>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="callout callout--editorial">
<div class="icon">!</div>
<div>
<div class="label">SEMANTIC OWNERSHIP</div>
<p><strong>Horizontal Axis:</strong> Story timeline, position, progression, structure, clock positions, acts, beats</p>
<p style="margin-top: 8px;"><strong>Vertical Axis:</strong> Story depth, dimensions (D0-D5), layers, thematic depth, psychological complexity</p>
<p style="margin-top: 12px;"><strong>Note:</strong> "Dimension" language refers specifically to vertical axis depth layers (D0-D5), not to axis-level framing.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="callout callout--editorial">
<div class="icon">⚠</div>
<div>
<div class="label">V3 DEPRECATION NOTICE</div>
<p>The <code>.dimension-horizontal</code> and <code>.dimension-vertical</code> CSS classes are <strong>formally deprecated</strong> in v3 and must not be used.</p>
<p style="margin-top: 8px;">All axis-level signaling must use Axis Callouts (<code>.callout--horizontal</code>, <code>.callout--vertical</code>) with full structure: icon, label, and content.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h3>Cross-Reference Links</h3>
<p>Links to other frameworks or sections use the <code>.cross-link</code> class for distinct styling: <a class="cross-link" href="#">Campbell's Hero's Journey</a>, <a class="cross-link" href="#">Save the Cat</a>.</p>
<h3>Structural Containers</h3>
<h4>Crosswalk Dimension</h4>
<p>Crosswalk dimension blocks organize dimension-specific analysis:</p>
<div class="crosswalk-dimension">
<div class="schema-label">Example Dimension</div>
<p>This is example content within a crosswalk dimension container. It provides visual grouping and subtle left-border accent.</p>
</div>
<h4>Framework Definition</h4>
<p>Framework definition blocks contain structured analytical content:</p>
<div class="framework-def">
<h5 class="minor-head">Definition</h5>
<p><strong>Structural Function:</strong> Example structural function description.</p>
<p><strong>Defining Logic:</strong> Example defining logic description.</p>
</div>
<h3>Tables</h3>
<p>Tables use alternating row colors, clear headers, and subtle borders:</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>ELEMENT</th>
<th>DESCRIPTION</th>
<th>EXAMPLE</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Header</td>
<td>Uppercase, bold, colored background</td>
<td>See above</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Data rows</td>
<td>Alternating backgrounds for readability</td>
<td>This row</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Borders</td>
<td>Subtle, consistent with theme</td>
<td>Around table</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h3>Checklists</h3>
<p>Checklists present grouped rules or requirements:</p>
<div class="checklist">
<div>First rule or requirement</div>
<div>Second rule or requirement</div>
<div>Third rule or requirement</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr/>
<!-- DARK MODE -->
<div class="section">
<h2>VII. DARK MODE</h2>
<p>The design system supports both light and dark modes with adaptive color palettes. Use the toggle button in the site header to switch themes.</p>
<h3>Dark Mode Principles</h3>
<ul>
<li>Semantic colors (amber, teal) remain consistent across themes</li>
<li>Neutral palette adapts completely (backgrounds, text, borders)</li>
<li>Gradients become more vibrant in dark mode (full opacity)</li>
<li>Shadows become deeper for better contrast</li>
<li>User preference is saved to localStorage</li>
</ul>
<h3>Technical Implementation</h3>
<p>Dark mode uses CSS custom properties (CSS variables) that are overridden when the <code>dark-mode</code> class is applied to the body element. JavaScript handles the toggle, state persistence, and initial theme detection based on system preferences.</p>
</div>
</div>
<footer>
<p>STORY COORDINATE COMPASS • DESIGN SYSTEM</p>
<p class="text-small">Version 2.0 Beta • Updated: </p>
</footer>
<script>
        // Shared theme toggle for Story Coordinate Compass
        (function () {
            const STORAGE_KEY = 'darkMode';

            function getToggleButton() {
                return document.getElementById('theme-toggle') || document.querySelector('.theme-toggle');
            }

            function setButtonState(isDark) {
                const btn = getToggleButton();
                if (!btn) return;
                btn.textContent = isDark ? '☀️ Light Mode' : '🌙 Dark Mode';
                btn.title = isDark ? 'Switch to light mode' : 'Switch to dark mode';
                btn.setAttribute('aria-pressed', String(isDark));
            }

            function applyTheme(isDark, persist) {
                document.body.classList.toggle('dark-mode', !!isDark);
                setButtonState(!!isDark);
                if (persist) {
                    try { localStorage.setItem(STORAGE_KEY, String(!!isDark)); } catch (e) {}
                }
                // Update neutral palette swatches if they exist
                if (typeof updateNeutralPalette === 'function') {
                    try { updateNeutralPalette(!!isDark); } catch (e) {}
                }
            }

            function readInitialTheme() {
                try {
                    const saved = localStorage.getItem(STORAGE_KEY);
                    if (saved === 'true') return true;
                    if (saved === 'false') return false;
                } catch (e) {}
                // Default to OS preference if no saved preference
                return window.matchMedia && window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches;
            }

            function init() {
                const initial = readInitialTheme();
                applyTheme(initial, false);

                const btn = getToggleButton();
                if (btn) {
                    btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
                        const isDark = document.body.classList.contains('dark-mode');
                        applyTheme(!isDark, true);
                    });
                }
            }

            if (document.readyState === 'loading') {
                document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', init);
            } else {
                init();
            }
        })();

        // Function to update neutral palette swatches when theme changes
        function updateNeutralPalette(isDarkMode) {
            const lightMode = {
                primaryBg: { color: '#FAFAFA', name: 'VAPOR', textColor: '#000000' },
                surface: { color: '#FFFFFF', name: 'WHITE', textColor: '#000000' },
                surfaceElevated: { color: '#F1F3F5', name: 'LIGHT GRAY', textColor: '#000000' },
                text: { color: '#222222', name: 'OBSIDIAN', textColor: '#FFFFFF' }
            };
            
            const darkMode = {
                primaryBg: { color: '#0F0F14', name: 'NIGHT', textColor: '#FFFFFF' },
                surface: { color: '#1A1A23', name: 'DARK SURFACE', textColor: '#FFFFFF' },
                surfaceElevated: { color: '#252533', name: 'DARK ELEVATED', textColor: '#000000' },
                text: { color: '#F0F0F5', name: 'LIGHT', textColor: '#000000' }
            };
            
            const colors = isDarkMode ? darkMode : lightMode;
            
            // Update primary background
            const primaryBgSwatch = document.querySelector('.neutral-primary-bg');
            const primaryBgHex = document.querySelector('.neutral-primary-bg-hex');
            if (primaryBgSwatch) {
                primaryBgSwatch.style.background = colors.primaryBg.color;
                primaryBgSwatch.style.color = colors.primaryBg.textColor;
                primaryBgSwatch.textContent = colors.primaryBg.name;
            }
            if (primaryBgHex) primaryBgHex.textContent = colors.primaryBg.color;
            
            // Update surface
            const surfaceSwatch = document.querySelector('.neutral-surface');
            const surfaceHex = document.querySelector('.neutral-surface-hex');
            if (surfaceSwatch) {
                surfaceSwatch.style.background = colors.surface.color;
                surfaceSwatch.style.color = colors.surface.textColor;
                surfaceSwatch.textContent = colors.surface.name;
            }
            if (surfaceHex) surfaceHex.textContent = colors.surface.color;
            
            // Update elevated surface
            const elevatedSwatch = document.querySelector('.neutral-surface-elevated');
            const elevatedHex = document.querySelector('.neutral-surface-elevated-hex');
            if (elevatedSwatch) {
                elevatedSwatch.style.background = colors.surfaceElevated.color;
                elevatedSwatch.style.color = colors.surfaceElevated.textColor;
                elevatedSwatch.textContent = colors.surfaceElevated.name;
            }
            if (elevatedHex) elevatedHex.textContent = colors.surfaceElevated.color;
            
            // Update text
            const textSwatch = document.querySelector('.neutral-text');
            const textHex = document.querySelector('.neutral-text-hex');
            if (textSwatch) {
                textSwatch.style.background = colors.text.color;
                textSwatch.style.color = colors.text.textColor;
                textSwatch.textContent = colors.text.name;
            }
            if (textHex) textHex.textContent = colors.text.color;
        }
    </script>

  </div>
</PortalLayout>
